sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K784010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a construct containing an [[Part:BBa_K784008|MCS followed by a tac promoter]] followed by the [[Part:BBa_K784005|theophylline riboswitch]] fused to mCherry. The construct was created using [http://openwetware.org/wiki/Assembly_pcr Assembly pcr]. This construct was used to characterize the relationship between the theophylline concentration and the level of translation of mCherry fused to the theophylline riboswitch.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ilya Vainberg Slutskin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: [http://openwetware.org/wiki/Assembly_pcr Assembly pcr] product of [[Part:BBa_K784008|MCS+tac promoter]] and [[Part:BBa_K784005|theophylline riboswitch]].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The coding region of the fused protein may have effect on the riboswitch function.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K784009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a construct containing an [[Part:BBa_K784008|MCS followed by a tac promoter]] followed by the [[Part:BBa_K784005|theophylline riboswitch]]. This construct is one of the two fragments used for the [http://openwetware.org/wiki/Assembly_pcr Assembly pcr] of the [[Part:BBa_K784005|theophylline riboswitch]] with different proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ilya Vainberg Slutskin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was received in a pUC19 plasmid from [http://www.gallivanlab.org/ Gallivan lab].

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mCherry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: mRFP (DsRed) derived, altered to be a biobrick by removing a PstI site and adding in the ends.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ytwang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: mCherry from Roger Y. Tsien's lab, altered to be BioBrick compatible
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Made a point mutation to eliminate a PstI site in the middle and then added BioBrick ends using PCR.

Sequenced using primers that bind to the pSB1A2 plasmid on either side of the brick.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K784012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This part has been created by deleting the aptamer and the additional 5' UTR regions of the [[Part:BBa_K784005|theophylline riboswitch]] using PCR. In addition, the deleted regions were replaced by a spacer region, which was added using the primers. The spacer region contains a PacI restriction site. As a result, only the RBS from the [[Part:BBa_K784005|theophylline riboswitch]] remains.
This part is the result of an insertion mutation to [[Part:BBa_K784007|BBa_K784007]].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ilya Vainberg Slutskin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The spacer region was designed to have minimal secondary structures. In particular, it was designed to have minimal base pairs in the with the RBS, in order to keep it free for interaction with the ribosome. The PacI restriction site in the spacer region was used to self ligate the PCR product, which was a complete plasmid without the aptamer and the additional 5' UTR regions of the [[Part:BBa_K784005|theophylline riboswitch]].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There is no source for this part. The RBS is the one used in the [[Part:BBa_K784005|theophylline riboswitch]].
